I have never given a poor review, but in all honesty, I found this recipe disappointing. My boyfirend and I really like beets, and so we thought we'd just add this to our recipes to try out when beets are in season. Our main issue is that the beet overpowered everything else and that in the end the soup just tasted like pureed beet, without any of the pleasure of the textureof freshly steamed or roasted beets. The soup even overwhelmed the squash. In the end we felt like it would have been better to have just had roasted beets rather than to go to all the trouble and preparation. Though it certain does have a wonderful presentation with the squash. As I was trying to figure out what to do with all the left overs I did come up with two different solutions, that I will put out there for those of you who are still curious to try out the recipe but that may share our disappointment. 1st variation is to add some of the beet soup to a potato leek soup, and then you can freeze the left overs with great success. 2nd variation is to simply add some sour cream and grated beet and turn it into a soupy borscht inspired bastardization, which is nonetheless very tasty.

