Rating: 4
At the request of our dad, this was our first course at Thanksgiving, It was served to a group of professed beet haters - myself somewhat included. I made it ahead of time, which I think is key, as it gives the soup a chance to develop its full flavor, and you can decide if you need to add anything. I made it up to the point of adding the salt and pepper, and then refrigerated it for 1.5 days. It came off as too sweet and bland, so I used the roasted garlic/onion suggestion and added salt and pepper to taste. I also served it with Sour Cream for people to top with if they desired (it adds a bit more oomph to the soup). Not only was the presentation beautiful, everyone at the table, including 7 & 5 year olds, and 35 year long beet haters, thought it was one of the best things they had ever eaten. It is definitely a repeat at our table. It is very filling, so I don't recommend it before a big meal, but it was fantastic!!! It's easy to make ahead - even the squash can be cooked a few hours before hand and then reheated before serving. Just watch out for the beet-red stains!!!

